&lt;h1 id="no-truth-can-be-justified"&gt;No Truth Can Be Justified&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Oct 15 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;lsquo;Knowledge&amp;rsquo; is just our best guess at the time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brett:&lt;/strong&gt;
Initial guesses at what &amp;lsquo;knowledge&amp;rsquo; was all about amounted to what is known as the &amp;ldquo;justified true belief&amp;rdquo; vision of knowledge, and it&amp;rsquo;s still the most prevalent idea today. Anyone who calls themself a &lt;strong&gt;Bayesian&lt;/strong&gt; is a justified true believer.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>It’s Rare to Have Competing, Viable, Scientific Theories</title><link>https://linguista.cn/naval/orig/its-rare-to-have-competing-viable-scientific-theories/</link><pubDate>Tue, 11 May 2021 18:31:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguista.cn/naval/orig/its-rare-to-have-competing-viable-scientific-theories/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://linguista.cn/naval/zh/its-rare-to-have-competing-viable-scientific-theories.zh/"&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
